Only one patient had a normal CXR. She was one of four survivors. Another survivor had right middle lobe consolidation, but the chest CT scan taken 1 day later showed more extensive disease (Figure 1, Figure 2
). A repeat CT scan 11 days later (Fig 3
), when the patient was clinically much improved, showed partial resolution of the consolidation and dilated bronchi. Four patients developed pneumothoraces (one bilateral, one with a pneumomediastinum) while ventilated. These were treated by chest drainage.
